{"id":"ah","term":"Ah!","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>An exclamation of sorrow or regret (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 35:25\">Ps. 35:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 1:4\">Isa. 1:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 1:24\">24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 1:6\">Jer. 1:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 22:18\">22:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 15:29\">Mark 15:29</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Psalms 35:25","Isaiah 1:4","Isaiah 1:24","Jeremiah 1:6","Jeremiah 22:18","Mark 15:29"]}